recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2021 2 Series (230i, 230i xDrive, M240i, M240i xDrive), 330e, 330e Xdrive, 4 Series Coupe (430i, 430i xDrive, M440i xDrive) M4 Coupe, M4 Competition Coupe, BMW 4 Series Convertible (430i, M440i), BMW X1 sDrive28i, xDrive28i, 2 Series Gran Coupe (228i, 228i xDrive, M235i xDrive), M2 Competition Coupe, 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, M340i xDrive, M3, M3 Competition, 530i, 530i xDrive, 540i, 540i xDrive, MINI Hardtop 2 Door (Cooper, CooperS, JCW), X2 sDrive28i, X2 xDrive28i, X2 M35i, Z4 sDrive30i, Z4 M40i, MINI Hardtop 2 Door (Cooper SE), MINI Convertible (Cooper, Cooper S, JCW), MINI Clubman (Cooper S, Cooper S All4, JCW), MINI Countryman (Cooper, Cooper All4, Cooper S, Cooper S All4, JCW All4), Rolls Royce Ghost, MINI Countryman (Cooper S E All4), Rolls Royce Phantom, Rolls Royce Cullinan, and Toyota Supra vehicles.  The passenger seat belt Automatic Locking Retractor (ALR) may deactivate early, before the webbing fully retracts.  As such, these assemblies fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: During a crash, a seat belt retractor that does not function as intended increases the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect the seat belt retractors (including the seat belts) and, if necessary, replace the retractors, free of charge.   Owner notification letters were mailed on September 3, 2021.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417; 1-866-825-1525 (MINI); 1-877-877-3735 (Rolls Royce); and 1-888-270-9371 (Toyota).
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2020-2021 8 Series Coupe, Grand Coupe and convertible 840i, 840i xDrive, M850i xDrive, M8 and 740 Li, 740 Li xDrive, 750 Li xDrive, M760 Li xDrive, X6 sDrive40i, X6 xDrive40i, X6 xdrive50i, X6 M50i, X6M, and 2019-2021 X5 sDrive40i, X5 xDrive40i, X5 xDrive50i, X5 M50i, X5M, X7 xDrive40i, X7 xDrive50i, X7 M50i, and 2021 M3, M3 Competition, M4 Coupe, M4 Competition Coupe, X5 xDrive45e, 745 Le xDrive.  The rotor and shaft within the integrated brake system may not have been welded properly and could separate during a hard braking event, possibly resulting in a loss of the Antilock Brake System (ABS) and braking assistance.
recalls.Consequence: A loss of ABS and a reduction in braking assistance can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will replace the integrated brake system, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on May 25, 2021.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2021 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, M3, and 330e xDrive vehicles.   The bolt securing the seat belt assembly to the frame was not tightened to specification.
recalls.Consequence: An improperly installed seat belt assembly may not restrain an occupant as expected, increasing the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the front seat belt buckle assembly connection and, if necessary, replace it, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on June 25, 2021.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: Rear Differential Leaking/Failure
issues.description: Multiple reports of rear differential leaking oil and complete failure, particularly in Competition models. Some owners report differential replacement needed within first 10,000 miles.
symptoms: Complete loss of power to rear wheels
issues.fix_description: Replace rear differential assembly and seals. BMW has issued revised parts for some cases.
issues.prevention: Regular differential service, avoid aggressive launches, monitor for leaks during inspections

issues.title: Transmission Overheating and Limp Mode
issues.description: 8-speed automatic transmission entering limp mode due to overheating, especially during track use or aggressive driving. Some cases require complete transmission replacement.
issues.fix_description: Software update, transmission cooler upgrade, or complete transmission replacement depending on severity
issues.prevention: Allow proper warm-up, use appropriate driving modes, regular transmission service

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption reported in S58 engines, with some owners needing to add oil every 1,000-2,000 miles despite no visible leaks.
issues.fix_description: Engine inspection, piston ring replacement, or valve stem seal replacement as needed
issues.prevention: Regular oil level checks, use BMW approved oil, monitor consumption patterns

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Roof Cracking
issues.description: Premature cracking of the carbon fiber roof panel, particularly around mounting points and edges. More common in vehicles exposed to extreme temperature changes.
issues.fix_description: Complete carbon fiber roof replacement, typically covered under warranty
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature exposure, regular inspection, protective coating

issues.title: Brake Pedal Feel Issues
issues.description: Inconsistent brake pedal feel, spongy brakes, and reduced braking performance. Some cases related to brake fluid contamination or air in the system.
issues.fix_description: Brake system bleeding, brake fluid replacement, or brake component replacement
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, avoid moisture contamination, proper brake bedding

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: iDrive 8 system freezing, black screen, or becoming unresponsive. Software glitches affecting navigation, audio, and climate controls.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, system reset, or infotainment unit replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid extreme temperatures, proper system shutdown

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: High-pressure fuel pump failures causing engine stalling, rough idle, and reduced power. More common in early production vehicles.
issues.fix_description: High-pressure fuel pump replacement with updated part number
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, regular fuel system cleaning, avoid running on low fuel

issues.title: Adaptive Suspension Malfunction
issues.description: Adaptive M suspension system failures, including strut leaks and electronic control issues. Warning lights and loss of adjustability reported.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty struts, repair wiring, or update suspension control software
issues.prevention: Avoid severe impacts, regular inspection, proper tire pressure maintenance

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: Wastegate actuator rattle on cold starts, particularly in twin-turbo S58 engines. Can indicate wastegate arm wear or actuator issues.
issues.fix_description: Turbocharger wastegate actuator replacement or complete turbo rebuild
issues.prevention: Proper warm-up procedures, quality oil changes, avoid aggressive driving when cold

issues.title: Door Handle Electronic Failures
issues.description: Electronic door handle malfunctions, handles not extending properly, or becoming stuck in extended position. More common in cold weather.
issues.fix_description: Door handle actuator replacement or mechanism lubrication
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication, avoid ice buildup, gentle operation in cold weather

editorial.tagline: The ultimate driving machine reinvented for purists
editorial.hero_blurb: The G80 M3 delivers 473-503 horsepower of twin-turbo fury wrapped in controversial styling. BMW's latest super sedan pushes boundaries with track-bred performance and everyday usability.
editorial.essence: This is BMW's most powerful production M3 ever, featuring the legendary S58 engine that transforms quiet commutes into adrenaline-fueled experiences. The G80 represents the pinnacle of M Division's engineering prowess, offering both Competition Package brutality and daily driver refinement.
editorial.heritage: Continuing 35 years of M3 legacy, the G80 builds on the E30's racing DNA through generations of evolution. This sixth-generation M3 carries forward the tradition of transforming BMW's 3 Series into a track-ready weapon while maintaining its sedan practicality.
editorial.design_philosophy: BMW's designers embraced polarizing aesthetics with the massive kidney grilles, creating an aggressive stance that announces the car's performance intentions. The wide fenders, carbon fiber accents, and purposeful aero elements prioritize function over beauty, reflecting the track-first mentality.
editorial.motorsport_history: The M3 nameplate was born from BMW's need for a homologation special in DTM racing. While the G80 hasn't yet proven itself on professional circuits, it carries the racing DNA of its predecessors that dominated touring car championships worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The S58 twin-turbo straight-six delivers relentless power with minimal lag, building boost like a naturally aspirated engine but with modern efficiency. It's a masterpiece of engineering that maintains the M3's signature smoothness while delivering devastating acceleration.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed ZF automatic shifts with precision and aggression in Sport+ mode, while offering seamless comfort in daily driving. Manual mode provides crisp, immediate responses that let you extract every ounce of performance from the S58 engine.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Adaptive M suspension delivers remarkable body control without sacrificing ride quality, while the rear-biased xDrive system maintains the M3's playful character. The chassis feels planted and predictable at the limit, inspiring confidence through sweeping corners.
editorial.steering_feel: Variable ratio steering offers precise feedback and appropriate weight, though it lacks the raw communication of hydraulic systems. The front end responds immediately to inputs, providing the surgical precision needed for track work.
editorial.brake_confidence: M Compound brakes deliver fade-resistant stopping power with excellent pedal feel and modulation. The system provides tremendous confidence under hard use, with consistent performance lap after lap on track.
editorial.sound_signature: The S58 produces a sophisticated straight-six growl that builds to an aggressive wail under full acceleration. The M Sport exhaust adds dramatic pops and crackles on overrun, creating an intoxicating soundtrack that's both refined and menacing.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance enthusiasts who want the ultimate daily driver that can dominate track days while comfortably handling family duties and business meetings.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Traditional BMW purists who prioritize understated elegance, rear-wheel drive purists, or buyers seeking maximum fuel economy in a luxury sedan.
editorial.buyers_summary: The G80 M3 represents peak M3 performance with controversial styling that grows on you over time. Focus on Competition models for maximum performance, and don't overlook the exceptional build quality and technology package.

expertReviews.title: Time to UPGRADE? - G80 M3 Competition Review
pros: 510 horsepower S58 engine with excellent power delivery
X-drive system provides confidence and grip while maintaining rear-bias character
Excellent daily usability with 35+ MPG fuel economy
Refined handling that feels more mature than previous generation
Switchable drivetrain modes including rear-wheel drive mode
Comfortable seats and improved ergonomics for daily driving
cons: Controversial large grille design
Sound quality not as good as previous generations
Heavier than previous M3
Less raw and chaotic than older M cars
Requires exhaust upgrade for better sound
expertReviews.verdict: The G80 M3 Competition represents BMW M's evolution into a more refined, daily-usable sports sedan. While it loses some of the raw character of previous generations, it gains significantly in usability, fuel economy, and all-weather capability. The X-drive system and switchable modes make it both accessible and engaging. For existing F80/F82 owners, it's a compelling upgrade that maintains M DNA while adding modern refinement.

expertReviews.title: BMW M3 Competition Review (G80) | Is this the best M3 yet ...
pros: Incredible S58 twin-turbo engine with 510hp/650Nm torque
Exceptional acceleration and performance

Comfortable daily driving capability

expertReviews.verdict: The reviewer is completely smitten with the G80 M3, calling it his new favorite car. Despite some criticisms about weight and styling, the incredible S58 engine performance, excellent handling, and daily usability make this an outstanding sports sedan. The reviewer would consider selling everything to own one, especially in Touring form.

expertReviews.title: Does The G80 BMW M3 Still FEEL Like An ///M Car? *M3 ...
pros: 510 horsepower 3.0L twin-turbo straight-six engine with 650 Nm of torque
Excellent rear styling and aggressive diffuser with quad exhaust
Impressive technology including drift analysis mode and intuitive infotainment
Functional aerodynamics with carbon fiber roof and performance ducting
Good practicality for a performance car with decent luggage space
xDrive system provides better traction off the line
cons: Highly controversial front grille design (beaver teeth/rabbit teeth)
Staggered wheel sizes (19-inch front, 20-inch rear) create visual imbalance
Overly complex mirror design with too many styling lines
In-your-face exterior color (Sao Paulo Yellow)
Interior color scheme may be too bold for some buyers
Limited rear passenger space for a midsize sedan
expertReviews.verdict: The G80 M3 Competition xDrive delivers exceptional performance with 510 horsepower and maintains the M3's performance DNA, but the controversial styling, particularly the massive front grille, remains divisive. While BMW has succeeded in creating a talking point and maintaining raw performance credentials without hybrid assistance, the polarizing design may overshadow the car's impressive capabilities for some buyers.

expertReviews.title: 2025 BMW M3 Competition xDrive - POV Test Drive (Binaural Audio)
Owning My BMW G80 M3 - 1000 MILE HONEST REVIEW
pros: Excellent carbon bucket seat ergonomics and comfort for long drives
Smooth and refined gearbox operation
Beautiful paintwork and overall appearance
Very capable as a daily driver GT car
Good handling and feedback compared to F-series
cons: Very small fuel tank requiring frequent refueling
Carbon bucket seats difficult to get in and out of
Gearbox feels like a computer game, lacks engagement
Less involving driving experience than F-series M cars
expertReviews.verdict: After 3 weeks and 1000 miles, the G80 M3 proves to be an excellent daily driver that surprised the owner with its comfort and refinement. While the carbon bucket seats are challenging to access, they provide exceptional support for long journeys. The main drawback is the small fuel tank requiring frequent stops, but overall the car excels as a mature, comfortable GT car that's easy to live with day-to-day.

expertReviews.title: The G80 BMW M3 Competition is the HOTTEST selling AWD ...
pros: 503 horsepower 3.0L twin-turbo straight six
Isle of Man green paint looks stunning
Excellent seat comfort and support
Quick 0-60 in 3.4 seconds
All-wheel drive capability
Premium features like laser headlights and carbon fiber accents
cons: No manual transmission option on Competition
Massive controversial kidney grilles
No ventilated seats at this price point
Rear calipers are not high-performance Brembos
Fake fender vents
No rear seat pockets
expertReviews.verdict: The G80 M3 Competition is a hot seller in the pre-owned market for good reason - it delivers serious performance with 503hp and AWD capability. While the styling remains polarizing with those massive grilles, the car has grown on many enthusiasts. The Isle of Man green example showcased impressive build quality and features, though some expected amenities like ventilated seats are missing at the $72k asking price.
